The paper presents a method for manipulating deformable objects using visual feedback and robotic end-effectors, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach is based on extracting features from RGB sensor streams, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The use of a visual feedback dictionary also suggests the involvement of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the approach on different cloth pieces with varying material characteristics indicates the use of statistical learning and data analysis (cs.LG). Finally, the use of robotic end-effectors suggests the involvement of control systems and automation (cs.SY).
